{{Infobox organization | name = Gnostic Society | logo = | founded_date = 1928 | founder = | location = Besant Lodge, 2560 North Beachwood Drive, Los Angeles, California, 90068, USA | origins = | key_people = | area_served = | focus = Study, understanding and personal experience of Gnosis | language = English | method = | revenue = | endowment = | num_employees = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = | homepage = [http://www.gnosis.org/ www.gnosis.org] }}
The '''Gnostic Society''' is an organization founded in [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]] in 1928, and incorporated in 1939, by John Morgan Pryse (1863-1952) and his brother [[James Morgan Pryse]] (1859-1942) for studies of [[Gnosticism]].{{Ref|1}}{{Ref|2}}{{Ref|3}} [[Stephan A. Hoeller]], PhD, noted author and lecturer and a leading exponent of Gnosticism as living religious practice{{Ref|3}}, has been director of studies since 1963,{{Ref|5}} and is also the [[Bishop]] of the [[Ecclesia Gnostica]].
The Gnostic Society is an educational organization "dedicated to advancing the study, understanding, and individual experience of Gnosis." Dr. Hoeller has been giving Friday evening lectures at the Gnostic Society in the Los Angeles area for over forty years.{{Ref|6}} Admission is free, relying on voluntary offerings. Many of these lectures have been recorded and are available in mp3 format.{{Ref|6}}{{Ref|7}}
