{{Infobox scientist |name = Kiyokazu Washida |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date|1949|09|02}} |death_date = |birth_place = [[Kyoto]] |nationality = {{flag|Japan}} |field = Philosophy |known_for = |prizes = Suntory Prize for Social Sciences and Humanities, History and Civilization (1989), Medal with Purple Ribbon from the Japanese government (2004) }} {{Nihongo|'''Kiyokazu Washida'''|鷲田 清一|Washida Kiyokazu}} is a Japanese [[philosopher]], specializing in [[clinical philosophy]] and [[ethics]]. He was born in Kyoto, Japan, and is currently a professor at [[Otani University]]. He was the 16th president of [[Osaka University]] and served on the screening committee of the [[Jirō Osaragi]] Prize, and the Suntory Prize for Social Sciences and Humanities.
